Negative Reviews:
As nothing is perfect in life, well Avenue Hostel and most of the hostels I visited arround the world does not skip this philosophy.

All hostels must implement little bit of discipline, such as informing all guests with no exception: 

1- To not turn room lights after 11 when they enter the room, instead using the private light on their bed;
2- To not have phone calls inside the room as guests and travelers can be sleeping at any hour of the day;
3- To not keep the door open;
4- To not give remarks to other guests, and enter in silly confrontations, rather flag the issue to the staff at the reception to be delt with on a professional manner; and
4- To keep the voice down when they are talking in the lobby, taking into consideration that their voice can echo the whole floor.
